casebody.data:
PICCOTT v. FLORIDA. No. 112,

Misc.

Decided October 17, 1960. Tobias Simon for petitioner. Richard W. Ervin, Attorney General of Florida, and George R. Georgieff, Assistant Attorney General, for respondent. Per Curiam.

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed. Treating the papers whereon the appeal was taken as a petition for writ of certiorari, certiorari is denied.
